sentences: Anna Hegner (1 March 1881 – 3 February 1963) was a Swiss violinist, music composer and pedagogue.
In 1908 she moved to Münchenstein and there she organized classical concerts in the Catholic Church (also performing as soloist) and organized summer concerts in the small gorge behind her house.
